IBADAN  – The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) under the auspices of its Director-General Mallam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo had empowered one hun­dred and eight unemployed youths in Ogun State with loans to enhance their agri­cultural businesses. Speaking during the ori­entation ceremony in Ogun State, the Director-General of NDE, Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo, said the selected beneficiaries were trained in various aspects of mod­ern agricultural produc­tion for a period of three months with two weeks of experiential training in both livestock and crops production. The NDE Director-Gen­eral represented by the NDE Ogun State Coordi­nator, Mr. Alao Babatunde Ismail, in his welcome address said “partici­pants have been trained in poultry production, cattle fattening, sheep and goat rearing, horticulture and dry season farming among others.” Kogi: Angry Mob Sets Police Barrack Ablaze Over Slain Boy NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others The DG said the loan schemes are means of providing farmers with seed money which would translate to increased ag­ricultural production and distribution system that would help to provide more profitable farm income, promote environmental stewardship and enhance the quality of life for farm­ers and their communities. Giving details of the loan schemes, Mr. Alao said that the target groups comprise all unemployed youth, from school leavers to graduates of tertiary in­stitutions, with a passion for agriculture as an enter­prise. According to the Direc­tor-General, “The manage­ment of NDE has approved the loan package of N100, 000 each for the 108 beneficiaries in four different schemes of the Rural Employment Pro­motion (REP)”.